A '''consensus site''' is a term in molecular biology that refers to a site on a [[protein]] that is often modified in a particular way. Modifications may be N- or O- linked [[glycosylation]], [[phosphorylation]],<ref>http://www.nature.com/nrm/journal/v2/n10/glossary/nrm1001-760a_glossary.html</ref> [[tyrosine sulfation]] or other.
